               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib238-1">Barsaum, Lu 'lu '2 , 510-36.
BSO, II, 80- 81 (J.M. Fiey).
Bibliographie sur lui et de lui : J.M. Fiey, dans PdO 13 (1986), 279-312.</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Gregory Bar Hebraeus was a celebrated writer and polymath of the Syrian Orthodox church. He was born near Melitene, the son of a doctor named Aaron. Their family fled to Antioch in 1234. He became a monk and then Bishop. He became the Maphrian of the Syrian orthodox church, and spent much time near the communities near the monastery of Mar Mattai. He wrote on a wide variety of topics, from theology to medicine.</note>
